---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config/site";

const title = `Cookie Notice | ${SITE.name}`;
const description =
  "Cookie Notice for CloudCostKit: consent, storage categories, ad-related cookies, and how to revisit your choices.";
const [emailUser, emailDomain] = SITE.email.split("@");
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/cookie-notice" robots="noindex,follow">
  <section class="card hero">
    <h1>Cookie Notice</h1>
    <p>
      This page explains the main cookie and browser-storage categories used on CloudCostKit, how consent choices work,
      and how to revisit those choices later.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Cookie and storage categories on this site</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li><strong>Required</strong>: core site behavior, security, and consent-state handling.</li>
      <li><strong>Preferences</strong>: optional browser-side storage such as saved calculator inputs.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics</strong>: aggregated usage measurement where enabled and allowed by consent.</li>
      <li><strong>Ads</strong>: ad delivery and, where permitted, personalized ads and related measurement.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">How consent works here</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      When consent controls are shown, they are used to manage ad and analytics choices before optional tracking or
      personalized advertising is enabled where required by law or configuration.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">How to revisit your choices</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Use the consent controls presented on the site when available.</li>
      <li>If you do not see them, clear site data for <code>cloudcostkit.com</code> and reload the page.</li>
      <li>You can also use your browser settings to block or remove cookies and site storage directly.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Third-party cookies and ads</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      If ads are enabled, third parties such as ad networks may set cookies or similar identifiers for ad delivery and
      measurement. Whether personalized advertising is allowed depends on consent settings and local requirements.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Related pages</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li><a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>: broader site data-handling explanation.</li>
      <li><a href="/terms/">Terms</a>: educational-use and site-use conditions.</li>
      <li><a href="/contact/">Contact</a>: how to ask a consent or site-operation question.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Questions</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      Questions about cookies or consent settings:{" "}
      <a href="#" data-email-user={emailUser} data-email-domain={emailDomain}>
        Email us
      </a>
      <noscript>
        {" "}
        ({emailUser} [at] {emailDomain})
      </noscript>
      .
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
